"{\"uid\": \"tribuneindia.com-news-parisolympics2024-eyes-on-sky-feet-on-ground\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Rohit Mahajan in Paris The humility of Neeraj Chopra, probably India's greatest living sportsperson, is truly humbling.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 122, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17, \"end\": 22, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999989377666865, \"rank\": 1.0622345826480086e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 42, \"end\": 55, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neeraj_Chopra\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Neeraj Chopra\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neeraj_Chopra\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neeraj_Chopra\"}, {\"begin\": 66, \"end\": 71, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9999926329031383, \"rank\": 5.781094154646718e-06, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Rohit Mahajan\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 13}, {\"ngram\": \"The humility\", \"from\": 23, \"to\": 35}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chopra, 26, is supremely confident, yet supremely self-deprecating - such people are rare.\", \"from\": 123, \"to\": 213, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Chopra\", \"from\": 123, \"to\": 129}, {\"ngram\": \"such people\", \"from\": 192, \"to\": 203}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A world champion, Olympics champion, with the looks of a rockstar, 10 years a role model - yet fame and wealth and hero-worship do not seem to have left a spot on his soul.\", \"from\": 214, \"to\": 386, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A world champion\", \"from\": 214, \"to\": 230}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympics champion\", \"from\": 232, \"to\": 249}, {\"ngram\": \"the looks\", \"from\": 256, \"to\": 265}, {\"ngram\": \"a rockstar\", \"from\": 269, \"to\": 279}, {\"ngram\": \"10 years\", \"from\": 281, \"to\": 289}, {\"ngram\": \"fame\", \"from\": 309, \"to\": 313}, {\"ngram\": \"wealth\", \"from\": 318, \"to\": 324}, {\"ngram\": \"hero\", \"from\": 329, \"to\": 333}, {\"ngram\": \"-worship\", \"from\": 333, \"to\": 341}, {\"ngram\": \"a spot\", \"from\": 367, \"to\": 373}, {\"ngram\": \"his soul\", \"from\": 377, \"to\": 385}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last night, after her son was beaten by Arshad Nadeem of Pakistan in men's javelin final at the Olympics, Chopra's mother said: \\\"The boy who won gold, he's also my child.\\\"\", \"from\": 390, \"to\": 561, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her son\", \"from\": 408, \"to\": 415}, {\"ngram\": \"Arshad Nadeem\", \"from\": 430, \"to\": 443}, {\"ngram\": \"Pakistan\", \"from\": 447, \"to\": 455}, {\"ngram\": \"men's javelin final\", \"from\": 459, \"to\": 478}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 482, \"to\": 494}, {\"ngram\": \"Chopra's mother\", \"from\": 496, \"to\": 511}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 535, \"to\": 539}, {\"ngram\": \"my child\", \"from\": 551, \"to\": 559}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These are Chopra's roots, and he says that he never forgets his roots - this keeps him grounded, he says.\", \"from\": 565, \"to\": 670, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Chopra's roots\", \"from\": 575, \"to\": 589}, {\"ngram\": \"his roots\", \"from\": 625, \"to\": 634}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Dekho ji...\", \"from\": 671, \"to\": 683, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\\"Dekho ji\", \"from\": 671, \"to\": 680}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When I started in sports, I never thought I'd reach this level.\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 747, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 702, \"to\": 708}, {\"ngram\": \"this level\", \"from\": 736, \"to\": 746}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Being from a village, from the family of a farmer, I rose and have reached here,\\\" Chopra said shortly after winning silver.\", \"from\": 748, \"to\": 871, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a village\", \"from\": 759, \"to\": 768}, {\"ngram\": \"the family\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 785}, {\"ngram\": \"a farmer\", \"from\": 789, \"to\": 797}, {\"ngram\": \"Chopra\", \"from\": 830, \"to\": 836}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 864, \"to\": 870}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So, when I manage to achieve thoda-bahut - some few minor things - and win a medal, I think about my journey.\", \"from\": 872, \"to\": 982, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"thoda-bahut\", \"from\": 902, \"to\": 913}, {\"ngram\": \"some few minor things\", \"from\": 916, \"to\": 937}, {\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 948, \"to\": 955}, {\"ngram\": \"my journey\", \"from\": 971, \"to\": 981}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I think about my roots, the small village I started from, my modest family (whose reach) was confined to a small area.\", \"from\": 983, \"to\": 1101, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my roots\", \"from\": 997, \"to\": 1005}, {\"ngram\": \"the small village\", \"from\": 1007, \"to\": 1024}, {\"ngram\": \"my modest family\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1057}, {\"ngram\": \"whose reach\", \"from\": 1059, \"to\": 1070}, {\"ngram\": \"a small area\", \"from\": 1088, \"to\": 1100}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All talk was limited to the village.\\\"\", \"from\": 1102, \"to\": 1139, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"All talk\", \"from\": 1102, \"to\": 1110}, {\"ngram\": \"the village\", \"from\": 1126, \"to\": 1137}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Such thoughts, said Chopra, keep him grounded, keep him motivated.\", \"from\": 1141, \"to\": 1207, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Such thoughts\", \"from\": 1141, \"to\": 1154}, {\"ngram\": \"Chopra\", \"from\": 1161, \"to\": 1167}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chopra is an authentic article, unchanged since we first met him eight years ago, there is a ring of truth in his words when he speaks about village, nation, country.\", \"from\": 1211, \"to\": 1377, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Chopra\", \"from\": 1211, \"to\": 1217}, {\"ngram\": \"an authentic article\", \"from\": 1221, \"to\": 1241}, {\"ngram\": \"a ring\", \"from\": 1302, \"to\": 1308}, {\"ngram\": \"truth\", \"from\": 1312, \"to\": 1317}, {\"ngram\": \"his words\", \"from\": 1321, \"to\": 1330}, {\"ngram\": \"village, nation, country\", \"from\": 1352, \"to\": 1376}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He does not do pretence, seems completely transparent - speaking in English holds a terror to him and he does not hide it; he knows the value of money and likes to earn it through endorsement, and he does not hide that as well.\", \"from\": 1378, \"to\": 1605, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"pretence\", \"from\": 1393, \"to\": 1401}, {\"ngram\": \"English\", \"from\": 1446, \"to\": 1453}, {\"ngram\": \"a terror\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1468}, {\"ngram\": \"the value\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1519}, {\"ngram\": \"money\", \"from\": 1523, \"to\": 1528}, {\"ngram\": \"endorsement\", \"from\": 1558, \"to\": 1569}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Could you answer a question in English, please, Chopra was asked by the venue media centre staff.\", \"from\": 1607, \"to\": 1704, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a question\", \"from\": 1624, \"to\": 1634}, {\"ngram\": \"English\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1645}, {\"ngram\": \"Chopra\", \"from\": 1655, \"to\": 1661}, {\"ngram\": \"the venue media centre staff\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1703}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chopra's eyes widened, he grimaced and said: \\\"Oh!\", \"from\": 1705, \"to\": 1754, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Chopra's eyes\", \"from\": 1705, \"to\": 1718}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now I need to motivate myself to speak in English, just how I motivate myself for competition.\\\"\", \"from\": 1755, \"to\": 1850, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"English\", \"from\": 1797, \"to\": 1804}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 1837, \"to\": 1848}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He did not even try to wash out the question about endorsement - and, indirectly, money - under a torrent of words about his love for the country.\", \"from\": 1852, \"to\": 1998, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the question\", \"from\": 1884, \"to\": 1896}, {\"ngram\": \"endorsement\", \"from\": 1903, \"to\": 1914}, {\"ngram\": \"a torrent\", \"from\": 1948, \"to\": 1957}, {\"ngram\": \"words\", \"from\": 1961, \"to\": 1966}, {\"ngram\": \"his love\", \"from\": 1973, \"to\": 1981}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 1986, \"to\": 1997}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I put my game on top priority after Tokyo and after Tokyo Games only I got the opportunity to get associated with brands,\\\" Chopra said when asked about the possibility of being distracted by sponsor commitments.\", \"from\": 2000, \"to\": 2212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2037, \"end\": 2042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.829992534882769, \"rank\": 0.20479881952058382, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my game\", \"from\": 2007, \"to\": 2014}, {\"ngram\": \"top priority\", \"from\": 2018, \"to\": 2030}, {\"ngram\": \"Tokyo Games\", \"from\": 2053, \"to\": 2064}, {\"ngram\": \"the opportunity\", \"from\": 2076, \"to\": 2091}, {\"ngram\": \"brands\", \"from\": 2115, \"to\": 2121}, {\"ngram\": \"Chopra\", \"from\": 2124, \"to\": 2130}, {\"ngram\": \"the possibility\", \"from\": 2153, \"to\": 2168}, {\"ngram\": \"sponsor commitments\", \"from\": 2192, \"to\": 2211}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It is usual that brands come after you (athletes), and if you get it, why will you leave that opportunity?\\\"\", \"from\": 2213, \"to\": 2321, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"brands\", \"from\": 2231, \"to\": 2237}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2254, \"to\": 2262}, {\"ngram\": \"that opportunity\", \"from\": 2303, \"to\": 2319}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Who, indeed, says no to money?\", \"from\": 2323, \"to\": 2353, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"money\", \"from\": 2347, \"to\": 2352}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Else, (without money), you will only work hard and destroy your body and will be left with nothing - shreer hi tootega khel khel kar, last mein kuch nahi rahega,\\\" Chopra said.\", \"from\": 2354, \"to\": 2530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2484, \"end\": 2487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asteroid_family\", \"score\": 0.9952312942360685, \"rank\": 0.004791555281045798, \"text\": \"kar\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asteroid_family\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asteroid_family\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"money\", \"from\": 2370, \"to\": 2375}, {\"ngram\": \"your body\", \"from\": 2414, \"to\": 2423}, {\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 2446, \"to\": 2453}, {\"ngram\": \"- shreer\", \"from\": 2454, \"to\": 2462}, {\"ngram\": \"last mein kuch nahi rahega\", \"from\": 2489, \"to\": 2515}, {\"ngram\": \"Chopra\", \"from\": 2518, \"to\": 2524}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said brand endorsements improve the profile of the sport and lure in kids.\", \"from\": 2531, \"to\": 2608, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"brand endorsements\", \"from\": 2539, \"to\": 2557}, {\"ngram\": \"the profile\", \"from\": 2566, \"to\": 2577}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 2581, \"to\": 2590}, {\"ngram\": \"kids\", \"from\": 2603, \"to\": 2607}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It also opens the way for kids, next generation,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2609, \"to\": 2668, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 2624, \"to\": 2631}, {\"ngram\": \"kids\", \"from\": 2636, \"to\": 2640}, {\"ngram\": \"next generation\", \"from\": 2642, \"to\": 2657}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When the question about his humility despite being the \\\"greatest living Indian sportsperson\\\" was translated into English for international media, Chopra hastened to clarify, in English, that that's not his claim: \\\"I am not saying that I am the greatest!\", \"from\": 2670, \"to\": 2923, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2742, \"end\": 2748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_people\", \"score\": 0.9999808897012147, \"rank\": 1.7721886799788183e-05, \"text\": \"Indian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the question\", \"from\": 2675, \"to\": 2687}, {\"ngram\": \"his humility\", \"from\": 2694, \"to\": 2706}, {\"ngram\": \"English\", \"from\": 2783, \"to\": 2790}, {\"ngram\": \"international media\", \"from\": 2795, \"to\": 2814}, {\"ngram\": \"Chopra\", \"from\": 2816, \"to\": 2822}, {\"ngram\": \"English\", \"from\": 2847, \"to\": 2854}, {\"ngram\": \"his claim\", \"from\": 2872, \"to\": 2881}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's just someone's opinion!\\\"\", \"from\": 2924, \"to\": 2955, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"someone's opinion\", \"from\": 2936, \"to\": 2953}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The opinion is not outrageous, for a gold and silver in the Olympics, sport's greatest festival and toughest contest, must count more than anything achieved in a 10-country sport.\", \"from\": 2957, \"to\": 3136, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The opinion\", \"from\": 2957, \"to\": 2968}, {\"ngram\": \"a gold\", \"from\": 2992, \"to\": 2998}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 3003, \"to\": 3009}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3013, \"to\": 3025}, {\"ngram\": \"sport's greatest festival\", \"from\": 3027, \"to\": 3052}, {\"ngram\": \"toughest contest\", \"from\": 3057, \"to\": 3073}, {\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 3096, \"to\": 3104}, {\"ngram\": \"a 10-country sport\", \"from\": 3117, \"to\": 3135}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Take your experience further with Premium access.Thought-provoking Opinions, Expert Analysis, In-depth Insights and other Member Only Benefits Already a Member?Sign In Now The Tribune, now published from Chandigarh, started publication on February 2, 1881, in Lahore (now in Pakistan).\", \"from\": 3140, \"to\": 3427, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3346, \"end\": 3356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chandigarh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.649681003454191e-23, \"text\": \"Chandigarh\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chandigarh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chandigarh\"}, {\"begin\": 3402, \"end\": 3408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lahore\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.644298469411795e-23, \"text\": \"Lahore\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lahore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lahore\"}, {\"begin\": 3417, \"end\": 3425, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"score\": 0.9999999999595275, \"rank\": 3.771959786871617e-11, \"text\": \"Pakistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your experience\", \"from\": 3145, \"to\": 3160}, {\"ngram\": \"Premium access\", \"from\": 3174, \"to\": 3188}, {\"ngram\": \"Thought-provoking Opinions\", \"from\": 3189, \"to\": 3215}, {\"ngram\": \"Expert Analysis\", \"from\": 3217, \"to\": 3232}, {\"ngram\": \"depth\", \"from\": 3237, \"to\": 3242}, {\"ngram\": \"other Member Only Benefits\", \"from\": 3256, \"to\": 3282}, {\"ngram\": \"a Member?Sign\", \"from\": 3291, \"to\": 3304}, {\"ngram\": \"The Tribune\", \"from\": 3312, \"to\": 3323}, {\"ngram\": \"publication\", \"from\": 3364, \"to\": 3375}, {\"ngram\": \"February\", \"from\": 3379, \"to\": 3387}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was started by Sardar Dyal Singh Majithia, a public-spirited philanthropist, and is run by a trust comprising five eminent persons as trustees.The Tribune, the largest selling English daily in North India, publishes news and views without any bias or prejudice of any kind.\", \"from\": 3428, \"to\": 3704, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3446, \"end\": 3452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sardar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5685628181141138e-30, \"text\": \"Sardar\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sardar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sardar\"}, {\"begin\": 3453, \"end\": 3472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dyal_Singh_Majithia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dyal Singh Majithia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dyal_Singh_Majithia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dyal_Singh_Majithia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a public-spirited philanthropist\", \"from\": 3474, \"to\": 3506}, {\"ngram\": \"a trust\", \"from\": 3522, \"to\": 3529}, {\"ngram\": \"five eminent persons\", \"from\": 3541, \"to\": 3561}, {\"ngram\": \"trustees\", \"from\": 3565, \"to\": 3573}, {\"ngram\": \"The Tribune\", \"from\": 3574, \"to\": 3585}, {\"ngram\": \"North India\", \"from\": 3624, \"to\": 3635}, {\"ngram\": \"news\", \"from\": 3647, \"to\": 3651}, {\"ngram\": \"views\", \"from\": 3656, \"to\": 3661}, {\"ngram\": \"any bias\", \"from\": 3670, \"to\": 3678}, {\"ngram\": \"prejudice\", \"from\": 3682, \"to\": 3691}, {\"ngram\": \"any kind\", \"from\": 3695, \"to\": 3703}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Restraint and moderation, rather than agitational language and partisanship, are the hallmarks of the newspaper.\", \"from\": 3705, \"to\": 3817, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Restraint\", \"from\": 3705, \"to\": 3714}, {\"ngram\": \"moderation\", \"from\": 3719, \"to\": 3729}, {\"ngram\": \"agitational language\", \"from\": 3743, \"to\": 3763}, {\"ngram\": \"partisanship\", \"from\": 3768, \"to\": 3780}, {\"ngram\": \"the hallmarks\", \"from\": 3786, \"to\": 3799}, {\"ngram\": \"the newspaper\", \"from\": 3803, \"to\": 3816}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is an independent newspaper in the real sense of the term.The Tribune has two sister publications, Punjabi Tribune (in Punjabi) and Dainik Tribune (in Hindi).\", \"from\": 3818, \"to\": 3979, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3920, \"end\": 3935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_Tribune\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Punjabi Tribune\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_Tribune\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_Tribune\"}, {\"begin\": 3940, \"end\": 3947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_language\", \"score\": 0.9999933961698618, \"rank\": 4.45359902041096e-06, \"text\": \"Punjabi\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3953, \"end\": 3967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dainik_Tribune\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dainik Tribune\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dainik_Tribune\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dainik_Tribune\"}, {\"begin\": 3972, \"end\": 3977, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hindi\", \"score\": 0.9999977794261311, \"rank\": 2.2205788799751354e-06, \"text\": \"Hindi\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hindi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hindi\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an independent newspaper\", \"from\": 3824, \"to\": 3848}, {\"ngram\": \"the real sense\", \"from\": 3852, \"to\": 3866}, {\"ngram\": \"the term\", \"from\": 3870, \"to\": 3878}, {\"ngram\": \"The Tribune\", \"fr